    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pagination splits large result sets across multiple API responses; rate limiting caps how many requests a client may send in a time window. Agents listing documents, walking search results, or bursting tool calls must implement pagination correctly and respect limits — or face truncated context, 429 errors, and banned keys."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pagination",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " returns data in pages via offset/limit, cursor tokens, or link headers. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rate limiting",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " restricts request frequency — servers respond with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "429 Too Many Requests",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and headers like "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Retry-After",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " or "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "x-ratelimit-remaining",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A research agent cannot load a million search hits in one call. RAG ingestion walks paginated catalog APIs. Parallel tool agents hit provider rate limits quickly. Correct pagination ensures complete data; rate-limit handling prevents failed runs and exponential backoff storms."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Complete data",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — iterate all pages for exhaustive retrieval"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Memory control",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — process one page at a time"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fair usage",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — rate limits protect provider stability"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Offset pagination",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — slow/unstable on large shifting datasets"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cursor pagination",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — cannot jump to arbitrary page"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Rate limits",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — increase latency when throttled"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Offset/limit"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def fetch_all_offset(client, path: str, limit: int = 100) -> list[dict]:\n    offset = 0\n    all_items = []\n    while True:\n        resp = client.get(path, params={\"limit\": limit, \"offset\": offset})\n        resp.raise_for_status()\n        batch = resp.json()[\"items\"]\n        if not batch:\n            break\n        all_items.extend(batch)\n        offset += len(batch)\n    return all_items"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cursor-based"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def fetch_all_cursor(client, path: str) -> list[dict]:\n    cursor = None\n    all_items = []\n    while True:\n        params = {\"cursor\": cursor} if cursor else {}\n        resp = client.get(path, params=params)\n        resp.raise_for_status()\n        data = resp.json()\n        all_items.extend(data[\"items\"])\n        cursor = data.get(\"next_cursor\")\n        if not cursor:\n            break\n    return all_items"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Link header pagination (GitHub-style)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "url = \"https://api.example.com/repos?page=1\"\nitems = []\nwhile url:\n    resp = client.get(url)\n    resp.raise_for_status()\n    items.extend(resp.json())\n    url = parse_next_link(resp.headers.get(\"Link\", \"\"))"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling rate limits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import time\n\ndef get_with_retry(client, url, **kwargs):\n    for attempt in range(5):\n        resp = client.get(url, **kwargs)\n        if resp.status_code != 429:\n            return resp\n        wait = float(resp.headers.get(\"Retry-After\", 2 ** attempt))\n        time.sleep(wait)\n    resp.raise_for_status()"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use it"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Always paginate",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " when API returns partial lists + continuation token"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prefer cursor",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " for large, live datasets (logs, tickets, commits)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Throttle agent parallelism",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " when approaching provider rate limits"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How to implement"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class RateLimiter:\n    def __init__(self, max_per_sec: float) -> None:\n        self.min_interval = 1.0 / max_per_sec\n        self._last = 0.0\n\n    def wait(self) -> None:\n        now = time.monotonic()\n        elapsed = now - self._last\n        if elapsed < self.min_interval:\n            time.sleep(self.min_interval - elapsed)\n        self._last = time.monotonic()\n\nlimiter = RateLimiter(max_per_sec=5)\n\nfor page in iter_pages():\n    limiter.wait()\n    process(page)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Examples"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Agent retrieves top 50 only — no full pagination needed\nresp = client.get(\"/search\", params={\"q\": query, \"limit\": 50})\nhits = resp.json()[\"results\"]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-world example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An indexing agent paginates a document API with cursor tokens, respects "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "x-ratelimit-remaining",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", slows down when remaining < 10, and checkpoints cursor in job state so retries resume without reprocessing pages."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Assuming empty page means done",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — check next_cursor / Link header"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Ignoring 429",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
